body:
Hi,

I am trying to parse a relatively large project that is generating a $shiftx operator. At some point in my flow I write it to verilog and then try to read it back. 
However, the verilog backend is treating it a blackbox and generating a cell with type \$shiftx, which is then not recognized by the parser. The simplest example I could come up with to reproduce is:

```verilog
module test(a, b, c);
  input [7:0] a;
  input [7:0] b;
  output [7:0] c;

  assign c = a[$signed(b) +: 8];
endmodule
```

A simple script to reproduce:
```bash
yosys shiftx.v -o foo.v; yosys foo.v -p "hierarchy -check"
```

code_blocks:
